headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored 23 points and Garry Harris made all six of his 3-point shots and added 22 points as the Orlando Magic held off a late rally to beat the Indiana Pacers 126-120 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Banchero, Harris lead Magic to 126-120 win over Pacers

headlines.description: — James Harden hit two 3-pointers and had a driving layup in the final four minutes against his former Brooklyn teammates and the Philadelphia 76ers stretched their winning streak to six games, outscoring the Nets 137-133 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: James Harden, Tyrese Maxey lead 76ers past Nets, 137-133

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma scored 20 of his 33 points in the fourth quarter to help the Washington Wizards rally for a 108-103 victory over the Houston Rockets Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kyle Kuzma has 33 points, Wizards beat Rockets 108-103

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo’s ability to keep getting to the free-throw line assured the Milwaukee Bucks would outlast the short-handed Denver Nuggets.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo helps Bucks beat short-handed Nuggets 107-99

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — The Minnesota Timberwolves looked unfazed by the long-awaited return of one New Orleans' star players or the Pelicans' mounting urgency to win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves spoil Ingram's return, top Pelicans 111-102

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Trae Young felt right at home in Oklahoma City against the Thunder.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young's 33 points, 11 assists lead Hawks past Thunder

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry threw his mouthpiece into the seats in frustration and got tossed himself for the surprising episode late in the game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poole beats buzzer with layup, lifts Warriors past Grizzlies

events.name: Utah Jazz at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — No offense to the Utah Jazz, but Damian Lillard said scoring 60 points against them was fairly simple. Not easy, just simple.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard has season-high 60 points, Blazers beat Jazz 134-124

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 26 points and 11 rebounds as the Toronto Raptors beat the Pacific Division-leading Sacramento Kings 113-95 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pascal Siakam scores 26, Raptors top Pacific-leading Kings

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James and the Los Angeles Lakers are starting to get key pieces of their lineup back as he makes his push toward becoming the NBA's all-time leading scorer.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis scores 21 points in return as Lakers defeat Spurs
